(607, 'Dissertation Fellowship in Marketing Area', NULL, '\nProgram Number:   73745\nTitle: Alden G. Clayton Doctoral Dissertation Proposal Competition\n \nSponsor: Marketing Science Institute\n \nSYNOPSIS:\r\nThe sponsor gives awards for the best doctoral dissertation proposals on important marketing subjects.\n \nDeadline(s):      08/06/2008\r\nEstablished Date: 04/08/2003\r\nFollow-Up Date:   06/01/2009\r\nReview Date:      02/14/2008\n \nContact:  Ross Rizley, Research Director\n \nAddress:    1000 Massachusetts Avenue\r\n                 Cambridge, MA 02138-5396\r\n                 U.S.A.\r\nE-mail:           rizley@msi.org\nWeb Site: http://www.msi.org\nProgram URL: http://www.msi.org/awards/index.cfm?id=60\nTel:              617-491-2060\r\nFax:\r\nDeadline Ind:     Receipt\r\nDeadline Open:    No\n \nAward Type(s):    Dissertation\r\n                 Prizes/Awards\n \r\nCitizenship/Country of Applying Institution: Any/No Restrictions\n \nLocations Tenable: Any/No Restrictions\n \r\nAppl Type(s):  Graduate Student\n \r\nTarget Group(s):  NONE\r\nFunding Limit:    $5,000\r\nDuration:         0\r\nIndirect Costs:   Unspecified\r\nCost Sharing:     No\r\nSponsor Type:     Miscellaneous Non-Federal\n \r\nGeo. Restricted:  NO RESTRICTIONS\n \nCFDA#:\n \nOBJECTIVES:\r\nThe dissertation must be no more than fifty percent completed at the time of submission and will be judged by prominent marketing academics on their importance and potential contribution to business and academia; quality of conceptual development; feasibility and appropriateness of methodology; and creativity.\n \nELIGIBILITY\r\nTo be eligible, students must be working toward a doctorate in marketing or a related field (e.g., organizational behavior, psychology, economics, strategy, management, finance etc.) at an accredited university.\n \nFUNDING\r\nThere will be a maximum of five winners. Each winner will receive an unrestricted cash prize of $5,000 designed to aid in the completion of the dissertation.  (cas)\n \nKEYWORDS: Economics\r\n                     Psychology\r\n                     Organizational Theory and Behavior\r\n                     Finance\r\n                     Marketing\r\n                     Business\n \nHow To Enter the Competition\nThe Marketing Science Institute is pleased to announce the 2008 Alden G. Clayton competition for the best doctoral dissertation proposals on important marketing subjects. This annual competition is named in honor of former MSI president Alden G. Clayton, who retired in 1986 after more than a decade of leadership at the Institute.\nTo be eligible, students must be working toward a doctorate in marketing or a related field (e.g., organizational behavior, psychology, economics, strategy, management, finance etc.) at an accredited university, and the dissertation must be no more than fifty percent completed at the time of submission. A letter from the primary thesis advisor approving the submission and certifying that the dissertation is no more than fifty percent completed must be received by August 15, 2008. Participation in other grant or award programs does not preclude being considered for the MSI AGC award. The competition is open to qualified doctoral students worldwide.\nSubmissions received after Wednesday, August 6, 2008, will not be considered. E-mail submission materials to Rizley@MSI.org. For blind reviewing purposes, please omit any identifying information from the proposal itself. Include a separate document containing your name and contact information, the title of your dissertation, and contact information for your thesis advisor/chair.\nThe maximum length of proposals is 25 double-spaced pages including tables, exhibits, and references. The first page should be a one-page, self-contained summary of the proposal. Proposals must include a brief statement of the problem area to be researched, relevant theory addressing that problem, hypotheses to be tested, methodology to be employed, analysis to be performed, and an indicative bibliography.\nSelecting the Winner\r\nProposals will be judged by prominent marketing academics on their importance and potential contribution to business and academia; quality of conceptual development; feasibility and appropriateness of methodology; and creativity. Research design aspects will play a particularly important role in the evaluation process.\nThe winner(s) will be announced in early November 2008. There will be a maximum of five winners. Each winner will receive an unrestricted cash prize of $5,000 designed to aid in the completion of the dissertation.\n\r\nProposals and inquiries should be addressed to:\nRoss Rizley, Research Director\r\nMarketing Science Institute\r\n1000 Massachusetts Avenue\r\nCambridge, MA 02138-5396\r\nPhone: (617) 491-2060\r\nEmail: Rizley@MSI.org\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2008-02-26 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(608, 'Joint Japan/World Bank Graduate Scholarship Progra', NULL, '\nProgram Number:   02058\r\nTitle:  Joint Japan/World Bank Graduate Scholarship Program\n \nSponsor: World Bank\n \nSYNOPSIS:\r\n The sponsor awards scholarships to individuals from World Bank member countries to undertake graduate studies at renowned universities throughout member countries of the Bank. Funding is used to cover the cost of completing a master\'s degree in a development-related field of study. Awards are given for one year at a time and may be extended to a second, consecutive year, provided that the academic program is longer than one year.\n \nDeadline(s):        03/31/2008\r\nEstablished Date: 03/28/1990\r\nFollow-Up Date:   12/01/2008\r\nReview Date:      11/26/2007\n \nContact:\n \nAddress:     Joint Japan/World Bank Graduate Scholarship Program\r\n                 MSN J2-204\r\n                 1818 H Street, N.W.\r\n                 Washington, DC 20433\r\n                 U.S.A.\r\nE-mail:       jjwbgsp@worldbank.org\n\nWeb Site:\nProgram URL:\n \nTel:              202-473-6849\r\nFax:              202-522-4036\r\nDeadline Ind:     Receipt\r\nDeadline Open:    No\n \nAward Type(s):    Student Scholarship\r\n                         Travel Abroad\r\n                        Training/Professional Development\n\r\nCitizenship/Country of Applying Institution:   Any/No Restrictions\n \nLocations Tenable:    Any/No Restrictions\n\r\nAppl Type(s):     Graduate Student\n\r\nTarget Group(s):  NONE\r\nFunding Limit:    $32,000   AVERAGE\r\nDuration:         2 YEAR(s)\r\nIndirect Costs:   Unspecified\r\nCost Sharing:     No\r\nSponsor Type:     Industrial Groups/Organizations\n \r\nGeo. Restricted:  NO RESTRICTIONS\n \nCFDA#:\n \nOBJECTIVES:\nThe Program’s objective is to help create an international community of highly trained professionals working in the field of economic and social development. The World Bank and the Government of Japan\r\nrequire the scholars to return to their home countries on completion of their study Programs and apply their enhanced knowledge and skills to contribute to the development process in their respective regions\r\nand communities. Applicants must propose a program of study related to development at the master\'s level, in fields such as economics, public administration, finance, planning, health, population, agriculture,\r\ninfrastructure, information systems and aquatic resources (provided that the focus of study is on public policy aspects of these fields), environment and natural resource management, education, and other\r\ndevelopment-related subjects.\n \nELIGIBILITY\r\n Eligible applicants must be nationals of World Bank member countries; be born after April 1, 1968; have at least two years of recent full-time professional work experience by March 31, 2008 after a university degree, in the applicant’s home country or in another developing country and usually in public service; and hold a bachelor\'s degree or its equivalent. Applicants must submit evidence of current unconditional admission to at least one development-related university master’s degree program and proof of application to a second such program. The universities must be located in any World Bank member country except the applicant’s home country. Preference is given to applicants with more than one admission. The Program does not support those who are permanent residents or nationals of\r\nindustrialized countries, nor those who have been residing in an industrialized country for more than one year.\n \nFUNDING\r\n The scholarship provides annual awards to cover the cost of completing a master\'s degree or its equivalent. The maximum period of funding is two years. The scholarship provides benefits for the recipient only, covering: economy class air travel between the homecountry and the host university at the start of the study program and one return journey following the end of the overall scholarship period. In addition to the ticket, scholars receive a US $500 travel allowance for each trip; tuition and the cost of basic medical and accident insurance usually obtained through the university; and a monthly subsistence allowance to cover living expenses, including books. The amount of the scholarship may vary depending upon the host country and the tuition charged by the host university. In recent years the annual value of a scholarship has averaged about US $32,000. (jap)\n \r\n \nKEYWORDS:  Developing/Underdeveloped Nations\r\n                          International/Global Development\r\n                          Agriculture\r\n                          Public Planning/Policy\r\n                          Population Studies\r\n                          Educational Studies--Developing Countries\r\n                          International Education/Training\r\n                          Economic Development\r\n                          Finance\r\n                         Corporate/Strategic Planning\r\n                         Natural Resources Management\r\n                        Socioeconomics\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-11-27 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(609, '最新讲座通知---11月9日', NULL, '\n讲座教授： 香港城市大学 Charles Ka Yui Leung教授\n \n讲座题目：Return Enhancing, Cash-rich or simply Empire-Building? An Empirical Investigation of Corporate Real Estate Holdings\n \n讲座时间：  11月9日星期五下午2点\n \n讲座地点：  光华裙楼2406\n  —————————————————————————————\nLecturer:  Prof. Charles Ka Yui Leung, City University of Hong Kong\n \nTopic:       Return Enhancing, Cash-rich or simply Empire-Building? An Empirical Investigation of Corporate Real Estate Holdings\n \nTime:       2pm. Friday, Nov 9\n \nVenue:     2406, Guanghuaqunlou\n—————————————————————————————\n相关论文：   Real-Estate-Corp-Govern-2007-Cheng-Du.pdf \n欢迎各位老师同学届时参加！\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-11-05 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(610, '最新讲座通知---11月2日', NULL, '\n\n\n\n\n主讲人：经济与管理研究院张大永老师\r\n             \n时   间：11月2日（星期五）下午14：00-15：30\r\n             \n地   点：光华裙楼2406\r\n             \n题   目：Oil Shock and Economic Growth in Japan: the Nonlinear Approach\n\n\n\n\n \n \n相关论文： nonlinear 2007.pdf\n—————————————————————————————————\n \n欢迎各位老师同学届时参加！\n\n\n\n\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-10-30 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(611, '最新讲座通知-10月30日（2）', NULL, '\n讲座题目：中国股市定价效率的约束与改进路径\n主讲人：        冯用富（西南财经大学金融学院副院长、教授、博导）\r\n                 董 艳（经济与管理研究院副教授，博导）\n时 间： 2007年10月30日晚7：30-9：30\n地 点： 金融学院会议室（光华楼1711）\n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-10-29 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(612, '最新讲座通知――10月30日', NULL, '\n主讲人：美国加利福利亚大学Rady管理学院 David A.Schkade教授\n \n主 题：A Survey Method for Characterizing Daily Life Experience: The Day Reconstruction Method\n \n主持人：经济与管理研究院 楚天舒老师\n \n时 间：2007年10月30日（星期二）上午9：30-11：00\n \n地 点：光华裙楼2205教室\n \n主 办：科研处 经济与管理研究院    \n \n相关论文：1、 2004_Science_Kahneman_et_al_DRM.pdf\n                      2、 2006_Science_focusing.pdf\n \n更多信息请参看： http://rady.ucsd.edu/faculty/directory/schkade/ \n____________________________________________________________________\n欢迎各位老师同学参加！\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-10-22 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(613, '最新讲座通知――10月26日', NULL, '\n\n\n\n\n主讲人：北京大学深圳商学院助教授 涂志勇博士\r\n             \n时   间：10月26日（星期五）下午14：00-15：30\r\n             \n地   点：光华裙楼2406\r\n             \n题   目：Why Do We Use the Dutch Auction to Sell Flowers?—Information Disclosure in Sequential Auctions\n\n演讲人简介：\r\n               \n涂志勇，男，美国匹兹堡大学经济学博士、法学硕士。现任北京大学深圳商学院助教授。曾任武汉大学经济与管理学院副教授。主要从事博弈论、机制设计、产业组织、拍卖理论和经济法的研究\n\n\n\n\n \n \n相关论文： flowerauction.pdf\n \n—————————————————————————————————\n \n欢迎各位老师同学届时参加！\n\n\n\n\n \n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-10-22 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(614, '最新讲座通知――10月12日', NULL, '\n主讲人：臧文斌\n\n\n时间：10月12日本周五14：00-15：30\n\n\n地点：光华裙楼2404\n\n\n讲座题目：Entry and Competition of Special Services in Local Hospital Markets\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-10-09 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(615, '关于城市经济学等四门课程上课地点变动的通知', NULL, '\n由于学校教室使用的临时调整，从下周起，以下三门课程的时间正式变动：\n \n1、黄霖老师：资产定价，周二下午5-7节，换到光华裙楼2407；\n \n2、李涵老师：实证产业经济学，周三下午5-7节，换到光华裙楼2407；\n \n3、傅十和老师：城市经济学，周四下午5-7节，换到光华裙楼2406；\n \n4、叶光亮老师：微观经济学（本科），周四下午5-7节，换到柳林B204;\n \n \n本变动从下周起（9月24日）在本学期内一直有效。请各位老师及同学相互转告。\n \n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-20 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(616, '最新讲座信息――9月21日', NULL, '\n讲座题目：Strategic Delegation and Evironmental Tax in a Mixed Oligopoly\n\r\n主讲人：王�P生 Leonard F.S Wang     ��立高雄大�W��用�����W系\nProf. of Econ. , National University of Kaohsiung\n \n时间：本周星期五 9月21日下午2：30\n地点：光华裙楼2404\n\n\npaper： Strategic Delegation and Environmental Tax in a Mixed Oligopoly.pdf\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-17 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(617, '硕博连读新生课程调整通知', NULL, '\n本学期星期三上午1到3节开设课程《马克思主义和当代社会思潮》，地点：研究生教学楼401，请同学们按时上\n课。\n\n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-16 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(618, '关于高级宏观经济学课程上课时间及地点更改的通知', NULL, '\n硕博连度2007级同学：\n请注意以下课程变动信息：\n课程名称：高级宏观经济学（硕博连读07级） \n任课教师：傅十和、董艳 \n上课时间：周二晚9---11节 \n上课地点： 光华裙楼2104 \n本门课程的上课时间地点按照上述变更进行。请相互转告。\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-10 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(619, 'Urban Economics Syllabus的开课通知', NULL, '\n本院本学期将开设城市经济学一课，课程信息如下：\n授课教师：傅十和\nE-mail：fush@swufe.edu.cn\n电话：8709－9206\n上课时间：周四 5－7节，共18周\n教室：光华楼裙楼2208\n答疑时间：周二 16：30—18：00 或预约答疑地点：黄楼301室\n课程主页：http://riem.swufe.edu.cn\n部分中文讲义和英文阅读材料可从该网址下载。网站在建设中。\n\n预备知识：本课程为硕博连读班城市与房地产研究方向学生的必修课和其他博士研究生的自由选修课。\n要求学生修过：（1）高级微观经济学；（2）动态优化；（3）计量经济学。\n\r\nGrading: Your final grade consists of five parts: problem sets, presentation, a referee report, a term paper, and a final take-home exam. Each accounts for 20%.\r\nThere is no unified, standard graduate textbook for this course. Therefore, we will draw materials from chapters of different books and papers from many journals. I have provided a tentative reading list below. The list will be updated from time to time. You must read at least one required reading material (marked with a * in the beginning of each item) for each topic.\r\nIMPORTANT!!!!\r\nAll the students should go to http://lists.repec.org/mailman/listinfo/nep-ure and subscribe the Urban and Real Estate working paper series. You will receive new working papers via email regularly. This service is free of charge. Each student is required to pick one working paper and write a referee report.\r\nIMPORTANT!!!\r\nFor those who will choose urban economics as your primary research field, you should visit www.lincolninst.edu and get to know the Lincoln Institute’s China Program. You are strongly encouraged to apply for the Lincoln graduate research fellowship next year.\r\nIMPORTANT!!\r\nYou are required to attend the Friday-afternoon seminars organized by RIEM if the topics are related to urban, regional, and real estate issues.\r\nIMPORTANT!\r\nThere will be no class on Sept.20, Thursday. You are strongly suggested to attend the ESRI exhibition in Chengdu to know some basics about the GIS software. The admission is free. Please sign up at http://www.esrichina-bj.cn/2007roadshow/index2.htm. 1\n \n欢迎各位同学选课！\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-09 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(620, '关于硕博连读新生正式行课时间的通知', NULL, '\n2007年新入学的同学将从本周三（9月12日）开始正式行课，具体课程安排见学院网站，链接为：http://riem.swufe.edu.cn/coursedetail.asp?id=5，请届时按时上课。\n另外，请2007年新入学的同学将各自目前的邮件地址、电话和学号尽快传到riem-grad@swufe.edu.cn。\n \n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-09-09 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(621, '关于2006级硕博连读学生博士综合资格考试安排的通知', NULL, '\n2006级硕博连读学生：\n根据西南财经大学硕博连读研究生培养工作的有关规定，2006级硕博连读学生博士综合资格考试工作将于近期开展，现将具体安排通知如下：\n\n西南财经大学2006级硕博连读学生综合考试安排表\n\n\n\n\n\n\n考试科目\n\n\n时 间\n\n\n地 点\n\n\n考试形式\n\n\n\n\n高级计量经济学\n\n\n2007年4月28日\n上午8：00－11：00\n\n\n黄楼326室\n\n\n闭卷\n\n\n\n\n高级微观经济学\n\n\n2007年4月28日\n下午14：00－17：00\n\n\n黄楼326室\n\n\n闭卷\n\n\n\n\n\n\r\n请同学们做好考试准备，特此通知。\n咨询邮箱：riem-grad@swufe.edu.cn\n相关链接：西南财经大学硕博连读研究生课程学习阶段培养流程\n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-03-20 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(622, '请选修甘犁老师《计量经济学》的同学注意', NULL, '\n请以下选修甘犁老师课程的同学尽快与甘犁老师联系（gan@econmail.tamu.edu）。名单如下：\n       黄翊、  陈炜煜、  邹伟伟、  祝立群、  赵勇 \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-01-18 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
(623, 'Student Fellowships', NULL, '\nThe Lincoln Institute of Land Policy International Student Fellowships\n \nThe Institute\'s China Program awards doctoral and master\'s thesis fellowships to graduate students attending universities in Asia and researching land and tax policy in the People\'s Republic of China. Fellows participate in a workshop in China to present their proposals and receive comments from an international expert panel. Applications for these China Program fellowships are due April 1, 2007. \nTo learn more, visit the fellowships Web site at http://www.lincolninst.edu/education/fellowships.asp or contact fellowships@lincolninst.edu.\n \n附件：lilp_doctoral_ann_prc_fy08.pdf\n      \n \n', NULL, 32, NULL, 1, 10, '2007-01-15 16:00:00', NULL, NULL),
